template.query:
SELECT DEMO.ACCESS_REVIEWS.ID, DEMO.ACCESS_REVIEWS.STATUS, DEMO.ACCESS_REVIEWS.ACTION, DEMO.ACCESS_REVIEWS.INITIALDECISIONREASON, DEMO.ACCESS_REVIEWS.REASON, DEMO.ACCESS_REVIEWS.UPDATED_AT, DEMO.ACCESS_REVIEWS.SUBMITTED_AT, DEMO.EMPLOYEES.NAME AS EMPLOYEE, DEMO.SYSTEM_ROLES.NAME AS ROLENAME
FROM DEMO.ACCESS_REVIEWS 
LEFT JOIN DEMO.EMPLOYEES on DEMO.ACCESS_REVIEWS.EMPLOYEE_EMAIL = DEMO.EMPLOYEES.EMAIL
LEFT JOIN DEMO.SYSTEM_ROLES on DEMO.ACCESS_REVIEWS.SYSTEMROLE_ID = DEMO.SYSTEM_ROLES.ID
WHERE DEMO.EMPLOYEES.REVIEWER_EMAIL = {{current_user.email}} 
AND (DEMO.ACCESS_REVIEWS.SUBMITTED_AT is NULL)
AND ({{!select4.value}} OR DEMO.ACCESS_REVIEWS.ACTION = {{select4.value}})
AND ({{!select1.value}} OR ROLENAME = {{select1.value}})
AND ({{!select2.value}} OR EMPLOYEE = {{select2.value}})
AND ({{!select3.value}} OR INITIALDECISIONREASON = {{select3.value}})
ORDER BY DEMO.ACCESS_REVIEWS.UPDATED_AT DESC, ID

template.label: Enter a reason for keeping the selected roles as is:

template.query:
select
  distinct count(*) over () as Total_Reviews,
  SUM(
    case when DEMO.ACCESS_REVIEWS.SUBMITTED_AT is not null then 1 else 0 end
  ) over () as Count_Submitted,
  SUM(
    case when (DEMO.ACCESS_REVIEWS.STATUS = 'Action Required' or DEMO.ACCESS_REVIEWS.STATUS = 'Rejected') then 1 else 0 end
  ) over () as Count_Action_Required,
  SUM(
    case when DEMO.ACCESS_REVIEWS.CLOSED_AT is not null then 1 else 0 end
  ) over () as Count_Approved
FROM
  DEMO.ACCESS_REVIEWS
  LEFT JOIN DEMO.EMPLOYEES on DEMO.ACCESS_REVIEWS.EMPLOYEE_EMAIL = DEMO.EMPLOYEES.EMAIL
where
  DEMO.EMPLOYEES.REVIEWER_EMAIL = {{current_user.email}}
